            "The rapid advancements in high-throughput biological data generation, encompassing areas such as genomics, transcriptomics, and proteomics, have necessitated a profound shift in biological research methodologies. Modern biological discovery is increasingly reliant on robust computational tools and analytical capabilities to process, interpret, and extract meaningful insights from vast and complex datasets [1]. In this context, proficiency in programming has become an indispensable skill for biologists.\n",
            "\n",
            "Python has emerged as a predominant language in scientific computing due to its readability, extensive library ecosystem, and versatility [2]. Specifically within bioinformatics, the BioPython project provides a comprehensive and mature framework, offering modules and functions for common tasks such as sequence manipulation, interfacing with biological databases, phylogenetic analysis, and structural biology [3].\n",
            "\n",
